  "_about": "Tool catalogue for the discover-project Workflow. Six new typed Tools are listed in TDD §Canonical Identifiers — Tool ULIDs (one query per Detect Step + the deterministic tenant-derivation Tool + the probabilistic infer-configuration-values Tool). All six are authored here as full entities with primary input/output JSON Schemas at schemas/tools/ (6 primary Tools × 2 schemas = 12 sub-schemas). WP-001 landed the first five (git-remote-read, read-package-json, read-pyproject-toml, read-ci-workflows, infer-configuration-values) and reserved the sixth (derive-consumer-tenant) via a _forward_declaration_ulid descriptor row; WP-002 flips that row to a full state=active entity backed by _discovery.tenant.Sha256CrockfordTenantDeriver and authors its schema pair. Two pre-existing Tools (entity-emitter, drift-detector) are declared via _reused_from rather than minting new ULIDs — they live in the marketplace's existing tool catalogue. Per ADR-003 (release-train two-class fidelity strategy applied here): the six Tools authored in this Workflow carry state=active + populated implementation_detail + error_catalogue cross-refs into failuremodes.jsonld. The _reused_from descriptor rows are NOT full Tool entities — they are excluded from brain-schema validation by the test_each_tool_passes_brain_schema filter on state=active. Tenant ULID is canonical for the marketplace tenant; ULIDs come byte-exact from TDD §Canonical Identifiers — Tool ULIDs.",
